This is my entry for the secret society contest.


A splinter faction of the former soviet republic is preparing to take over the world's goverments. Their sleeper cells have infiltrated all of the major governments around the world and they have secret bases scattered across the globe. We have located one of these bases through sattelite imaging. You and your team are to deploy to the remote Altai mountain range in Kazachstan and disable their base.




It's a standard bomb/defuse map with buyzones and 2 bomb sites.

features include:

-custom models

-custom textures

-custom skybox

-radar

The Alps - Bomb/Defuse by Dimension Studios
http://www.dimensionstudios.org/

Special thanks to the Orion team.
http://www.orion-project.net/

Introduction:
An influencial member of the Senate is sponsoring a resolution to establish a new international system of countering extremism. Supported in a wide range of countries, this resolution has the potential to deliver a serious blow to global terrorism. In an attempt to prevent such resolution from going into effect, a group of terrorists is planning on destroying Senator's recently inherited property in the alps mountains.

Terrorists' mission: 
Destroy the house by planting the C4 in the main house or in the abandoned mine underneath.

Counter-Terrorists' mission: 
Stop the terrorists from destroying the house.

Credits:
Project Director: Aldez
Level Design, Environment art: Aldez, Rickets007
Custom textures: Aldez, Nay0r, Aleksandr
Custom models: Orion team, Aldez, Bubbles
Soundscapes: Aleksandr
Bot navigation mesh: Barndoor

For more, full-sized screenshots please visit http://www.dimensionstudios.org/

This is still a work in progress but Very playable. 

 This map is trying to give the player the feel that he or she is in an alien complex.  It supports up to 44 people.  It also has close, medium and far ranges for all types of weapon play.  The sound  just adds to the effect of being in an disturbed area...  Theres a decent amount of I candy through out the map and you can Interact with the map with explosive and gas propelled canisters.  Feel free to jump into the stasis field while defend bomb site b, believe me its a trip.  (lay of the dope when you play this map)

 Any server hosts willing to try it out and post feed back would rock.   Anything worth adding to the map, Honestly...I will add no problem.  For people with Alpha impared monitors (crapy brightness like LCD monitor owners)  Please forgive how dark it is and just increase the brightness settings.  

LEVEL DESIGNERS: 

 If you would like to work on this project with me I HAVE NO PROBLEM WITH IT.  Any help to make this better would be well recieved.  If any mappers out there like the concept but feel as though they could piece this map together better than me...GOOD, let me know and I will send you the .vmf and be happy about it.

Thanks to interlopers.net for the support and knowledge on mapping.

DE_AGENCY by Jonathan P. aka Cacojo15 (released April 2010).

Another good Bomb/Defuse map for fans of narrow spaces!

Action here happens in any Office/Warehouse building. All space of this map is a narrow corridors, a wide network of ventilation and some small warehouses and halls. There are a lot of opening doors (with a creaking sounds) that serves as a factor of opponent's uncovering and allows to make some cunning ambushes ;-)

Note about Bombsites: In spite of the fact that Radar shows only one Bombsite (B), actually them here two is shown. Simply they are located one over another in rooms on different floors of the building.

Note about Bots: Despite certain complicating factors (a set of doors and vents) Bots play on the map rather surely. It seems that the .nav-file (included in .bsp) was carefully hand-tuned. One more plus to the map author :-)

Happy Frags... Play & Enjoy!
